solution.p:
Similarly, to find the equation of  f(g(x)), we start by rewriting the function  f(x)  with parenthesis around the input  x .
 f(x)=2(x)^2+e^{(x)}
Then, by the same reasoning as above, we simply need to put the out of  g(x), which is  3x+1, in place of the input of  f(x), which is again just  x . So, the other composition is given by
 f(g(x))=2(3x+1)^2+e^{(3x+1)}
